\f2\b\fs18 \cf4 \super 2\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub The islanders showed us unusual kindness. They built a fire and welcomed us all because it was raining and cold.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 3\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub Paul gathered a pile of brushwood and, as he put it on the fire, a viper, driven out by the heat, fastened itself on his hand.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 4\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub When the islanders saw the snake hanging from his hand,\'a0they said to each other, \'93This man must be a murderer; for though he escaped from the sea, the goddess Justice has not allowed him to live.\'94\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 5\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub But Paul shook the snake off into the fire and suffered no ill effects.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 6\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub The people expected him to swell up or suddenly fall dead; but after waiting a long time and seeing nothing unusual happen to him, they changed their minds and said he was a god.\
\
