\f2\b\fs18 \cf4 \super 7\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub There was an estate nearby that belonged to Publius, the chief official of the island. He welcomed us to his home and showed us generous hospitality for three days.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 8\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub His father was sick in bed, suffering from fever and dysentery. Paul went in to see him and, after prayer,\'a0placed his hands on him\'a0and healed him.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 9\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub When this had happened, the rest of the sick on the island came and were cured.\'a0
\f2\b\fs18 \super 10\'a0
\f3\b0\fs24 \nosupersub They honored us\'a0in many ways; and when we were ready to sail, they furnished us with the supplies we needed.\
